# Code Quality Tools

Enforce consistent code style and catch errors early with automated linting and formatting.

## Default Behavior

### ESLint for Static Analysis

Use ESLint with Angular-specific rules for catching errors, enforcing patterns, and maintaining code quality.

```json
// .eslintrc.json
{
  "root": true,
  "ignorePatterns": ["projects/**/*"],
  "overrides": [
    {
      "files": ["*.ts"],
      "extends": [
        "eslint:recommended",
        "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
        "plugin:@typescript-eslint/stylistic",
        "plugin:@angular-eslint/recommended",
        "plugin:@angular-eslint/template/process-inline-templates"
      ],
      "rules": {
        "@angular-eslint/directive-selector": [
          "error",
          { "type": "attribute", "prefix": "app", "style": "camelCase" }
        ],
        "@angular-eslint/component-selector": [
          "error",
          { "type": "element", "prefix": "app", "style": "kebab-case" }
        ],
        "@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars": [
          "error",
          { "argsIgnorePattern": "^_", "varsIgnorePattern": "^_" }
        ],
        "@typescript-eslint/explicit-function-return-type": "off",
        "@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any": "error",
        "no-console": ["warn", { "allow": ["warn", "error"] }]
      }
    },
    {
      "files": ["*.html"],
      "extends": [
        "plugin:@angular-eslint/template/recommended",
        "plugin:@angular-eslint/template/accessibility"
      ],
      "rules": {
        "@angular-eslint/template/click-events-have-key-events": "error",
        "@angular-eslint/template/interactive-supports-focus": "error"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### Prettier for Formatting

Use Prettier for consistent code formatting. Do NOT use ESLint for formatting rules.

```json
// .prettierrc
{
  "singleQuote": true,
  "trailingComma": "none",
  "printWidth": 100,
  "tabWidth": 2,
  "semi": true,
  "bracketSpacing": true,
  "arrowParens": "avoid",
  "endOfLine": "lf",
  "overrides": [
    {
      "files": "*.html",
      "options": {
        "parser": "angular"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

```
// .prettierignore
dist/
node_modules/
coverage/
.angular/
*.min.js
*.min.css
package-lock.json
```

### Separate Concerns: Linting vs Formatting

ESLint handles **code quality**, Prettier handles **code style**. Never mix them.

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    CODE QUALITY (ESLint)                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ✓ Unused variables                                          │
│  ✓ Type safety issues                                        │
│  ✓ Potential bugs (no-explicit-any, no-unused-vars)          │
│  ✓ Angular best practices (component selectors, lifecycle)   │
│  ✓ Accessibility in templates                                │
│  ✓ Import patterns and restrictions                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    CODE STYLE (Prettier)                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ✓ Indentation (tabs vs spaces, tab width)                   │
│  ✓ Quotes (single vs double)                                 │
│  ✓ Semicolons                                                │
│  ✓ Line length and wrapping                                  │
│  ✓ Trailing commas                                           │
│  ✓ Bracket spacing                                           │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Integration: ESLint + Prettier Without Conflicts

Install `eslint-config-prettier` to disable ESLint rules that conflict with Prettier.

```json
// package.json - required dependencies
{
  "devDependencies": {
    "@angular-eslint/builder": "^18.0.0",
    "@angular-eslint/eslint-plugin": "^18.0.0",
    "@angular-eslint/eslint-plugin-template": "^18.0.0",
    "@angular-eslint/schematics": "^18.0.0",
    "@angular-eslint/template-parser": "^18.0.0",
    "@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin": "^7.0.0",
    "@typescript-eslint/parser": "^7.0.0",
    "eslint": "^8.57.0",
    "eslint-config-prettier": "^9.1.0",
    "prettier": "^3.2.0"
  }
}
```

```json
// .eslintrc.json - add prettier at the END of extends
{
  "overrides": [
    {
      "files": ["*.ts"],
      "extends": [
        "eslint:recommended",
        "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
        "plugin:@angular-eslint/recommended",
        "prettier"  // MUST be last - disables conflicting rules
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### NPM Scripts

```json
// package.json
{
  "scripts": {
    "lint": "ng lint",
    "lint:fix": "ng lint --fix",
    "format": "prettier --write \"src/**/*.{ts,html,scss,json}\"",
    "format:check": "prettier --check \"src/**/*.{ts,html,scss,json}\"",
    "code-quality": "npm run format && npm run lint:fix"
  }
}
```

| Script | Purpose | When to Use |
|--------|---------|-------------|
| `lint` | Check for code quality issues | CI/CD, before commits |
| `lint:fix` | Auto-fix linting issues | Development |
| `format` | Format all files with Prettier | Development, after major changes |
| `format:check` | Check formatting without writing | CI/CD |
| `code-quality` | Format + lint in one command | Before commits |

### Pre-commit Hooks with Husky + lint-staged

Automatically lint and format staged files before every commit.

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install --save-dev husky lint-staged
npx husky init
```

```json
// package.json
{
  "lint-staged": {
    "*.{ts,html}": [
      "eslint --fix",
      "prettier --write"
    ],
    "*.{json,scss,css,md}": [
      "prettier --write"
    ]
  }
}
```

```bash
# .husky/pre-commit
npx lint-staged
```

```
Pre-commit workflow:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  git commit -m "feat: add user form"                        │
│                        │                                     │
│                        ▼                                     │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │  Husky triggers pre-commit hook                      │    │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │
│                        │                                     │
│                        ▼                                     │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │  lint-staged runs on STAGED files only               │    │
│  │  ├── ESLint --fix on *.ts, *.html                    │    │
│  │  └── Prettier --write on all                         │    │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │
│                        │                                     │
│              ┌─────────┴─────────┐                           │
│              ▼                   ▼                           │
│         PASSED               FAILED                          │
│              │                   │                           │
│              ▼                   ▼                           │
│        Commit proceeds     Commit blocked                    │
│                            (fix issues first)                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Rationale

1. **Consistency** - Every developer's code looks the same, reducing cognitive load in code reviews.
2. **Early error detection** - Catch bugs and bad patterns before they reach code review or production.
3. **Automated enforcement** - Rules run automatically, no manual review needed for style issues.
4. **Team velocity** - No debates about formatting, Prettier decides.
5. **Accessibility** - Angular ESLint template rules catch a11y issues in templates.

## Documented Exceptions

### 1. Disable Rules for Specific Lines

When a rule doesn't apply to a specific case, disable it inline with a comment.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Disable for specific line with explanation
// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any -- Third-party API returns untyped data
const response: any = await legacyApi.getData();

// ✅ Exception: Disable for block
/* eslint-disable no-console */
console.log('Debug info for development');
console.log('More debug info');
/* eslint-enable no-console */
```

**Always include a comment explaining why the rule is disabled.**

### 2. Skip Formatting for Generated Files

Some files are auto-generated and shouldn't be formatted.

```
// .prettierignore
# Generated files
src/app/api/generated/**
*.generated.ts

# Build outputs
dist/
coverage/
.angular/
```

### 3. Custom Rules per File Type

Different rules may apply to test files vs production code.

```json
// .eslintrc.json
{
  "overrides": [
    {
      "files": ["*.spec.ts", "*.test.ts"],
      "rules": {
        "@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any": "off",  // More lenient in tests
        "no-console": "off"  // Allow console in tests
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

### 4. Skip Pre-commit Hooks Temporarily

In emergencies, skip hooks with `--no-verify` (use sparingly).

```bash
# ✅ Exception: Emergency fix that needs immediate deployment
git commit --no-verify -m "hotfix: critical production bug"

# ❌ Never use as default workflow
git commit --no-verify -m "feat: new feature"  # Bad habit
```

## Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Using ESLint for formatting rules
{
  "rules": {
    "indent": ["error", 2],      // Prettier handles this
    "quotes": ["error", "single"], // Prettier handles this
    "semi": ["error", "always"]   // Prettier handles this
  }
}

// ❌ Disabling rules project-wide without reason
{
  "rules": {
    "@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any": "off"  // Defeats the purpose
  }
}

// ❌ Ignoring ESLint errors instead of fixing them
// @ts-ignore
// eslint-disable-next-line  // No explanation

// ❌ Committing with --no-verify regularly
git commit --no-verify -m "wip"  // Bypasses all quality gates

// ❌ Mixing formatting tools
// Using both Prettier AND ESLint formatting rules
// Using both Prettier AND IDE auto-format with different settings
```

## Editor Integration

### VS Code Settings

```json
// .vscode/settings.json
{
  "editor.formatOnSave": true,
  "editor.defaultFormatter": "esbenp.prettier-vscode",
  "[typescript]": {
    "editor.defaultFormatter": "esbenp.prettier-vscode",
    "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
      "source.fixAll.eslint": "explicit"
    }
  },
  "[html]": {
    "editor.defaultFormatter": "esbenp.prettier-vscode"
  },
  "eslint.validate": ["typescript", "html"]
}
```

