## CI/CD Integration

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml
jobs:
  quality:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
          cache: 'npm'
      
      - run: npm ci
      
      - name: Check formatting
        run: npm run format:check
      
      - name: Run linter
        run: npm run lint
      
      - name: Run tests
        run: npm test -- --no-watch --code-coverage
```

## Complete Setup Checklist

- [ ] ESLint installed with `@angular-eslint` packages
- [ ] Prettier installed
- [ ] `eslint-config-prettier` installed and added to extends (last position)
- [ ] `.eslintrc.json` configured with Angular rules
- [ ] `.prettierrc` configured with team preferences
- [ ] `.prettierignore` excludes build outputs and generated files
- [ ] NPM scripts added: `lint`, `lint:fix`, `format`, `format:check`
- [ ] Husky and lint-staged installed
- [ ] Pre-commit hook runs lint-staged
- [ ] VS Code settings configured for format-on-save
- [ ] CI/CD runs format check and lint

## Quick Reference: Common ESLint Rules for Angular

| Rule | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `@angular-eslint/component-selector` | Enforce component selector naming |
| `@angular-eslint/directive-selector` | Enforce directive selector naming |
| `@angular-eslint/no-output-native` | Prevent outputs named like DOM events |
| `@angular-eslint/use-lifecycle-interface` | Require lifecycle interface implementation |
| `@angular-eslint/template/accessibility` | Catch a11y issues in templates |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` | Prevent `any` type usage |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` | Flag unused variables |
| `no-console` | Warn/error on console.log usage |
